               <sense xml:id="Dmain" xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann"> quadril. I [amh. <foreign xml:lang="gez">ፈነቀለ፡</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> to </quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> overturn </quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> turn </quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> upside </quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> down </quote></cit> <ref cRef="Isenb." loc="195">Isenb. p. 195</ref>] <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> refodere </quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> rimari </quote></cit>, evertendo et invertendo res studiose <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> perscrutari </quote></cit> [<foreign xml:lang="ar">فقر</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> fodit </quote></cit>? <lbl expand="secundum">sec.</lbl> Lud. proprie dicitur de simiis quae „lapides partim e terra prominentes evertunt ac sub iis latentes vermiculos devorant“]: <foreign xml:lang="gez">እለ፡ ይፈነቅሉ፡ መቃብረ፡</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="grc">τυμβωρύχοι</foreign> <ref cRef="Chrys. ho. " loc="29">Chrys. ho.  29</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተሀውክ፡ ኵሎ፡ ዘውስተ፡ ቤታ፡ ወትፈነቅል፡ ወተኀሥሥ፡ አስተሓሚማ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Luc. " loc="15,8">Luc.  15,8</ref> <lbl expand="romanae editionis">rom.</lbl> (in <lbl expand="edidit">ed.</lbl> Platt <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተሀውክ፡ ወ</foreign> omissum est); Thomas apostolus <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘፈንቀለ፡ አጽልዕቲሁ፡ ወአብአ፡ አጻብዒሁ፡ ውስተ፡ ገቦሁ፡</foreign> M.M. f. 180. </sense>
               
            <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወፈንቀልዋ፡ ለሣዕር፡ ወኢረከቡ፡ ውዕየተ፡ ወኢምንተኒ፡</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote> ‘they overturned the grass but did not find any burning at all’ </quote></cit> <bibl><ptr target="bm:Tedros2015Yonas"/><citedRange unit="page"> 52 (348) l. 5 (ed.); 53 (349) l. 5-6 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> (‘The verb <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> fänqälä</quote></cit> in Gǝʿǝz is attested (e.g. Lk 15:8) but very rarely. It is common in Tǝgrǝñña’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Tedros2015Yonas"/><citedRange unit="page"> 53(349) n. 64</citedRange></bibl>) </sense>
